OL,6,FThe IOPC report said he "froze in the
OL,7,Fcrisis" and found he had a case to
OL,8,Fanswer for gross misconduct in respect
OL,9,Fof 10 allegations, including for
OL,10,Ffailing to respond and telling FA
OL,11,Fofficials, in what he later
OL,12,Facknowledged was a lie, fans had
OL,13,Fforced their way in.
OL,15,FThe report noted that allegations fans
OL,16,Fwere to blame for the disaster were
OL,17,F"wholly refuted" at new inquests into
OL,18,Fthe deaths, which in 2016 concluded
OL,19,Ffans had been unlawfully killed.
